Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Judgement=On Hell and Damnation
  - 166
---
Now, in this present time, man is set between heaven and hell, and may
turn himself towards which he will. For the more he hath of ownership,
the more he hath of hell and misery; and the less of self-will, the
less of hell, and the nearer he is to the Kingdom of Heaven.
